Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.19,0:17:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,simple things to be gracious, to be uh\Nto confirm for other people their joy in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.80,0:17:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,life, their value in life, that what\Nthey're doing is appreciated. See,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.16,0:17:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because whatever they're doing is there\Nis no scale of worth on on the things
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.91,0:17:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you do, action has no scale of worth.\NThe simplest thing can be of critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.52,0:17:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, somebody holds the dumpster up\Nfor you and your back is out and that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.64,0:17:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody hold the dumpster out for up\Nthe hill for you, you know, because
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.16,0:17:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you're worrying how you're going to get\Nit up there and then suddenly you find
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.03,0:17:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's up there. So those little joys of\Nlife. So you reflect back to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.40,0:17:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you envision um as the\Nqualities that you admire. Yeah. In that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.40,0:17:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,way you quickly go up the scale of\Nconsciousness which just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.44,0:17:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How long does it take? People think,\N"Oh, it's going to take lifetimes and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.55,0:18:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes and lifetimes."\NWell, the way it used to be, it probably
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.91,0:18:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,did.\NThe knowledge about consciousness was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.55,0:18:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely limited.\NA few gurus existed, but they lived in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.52,0:18:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,ashrams and enclaves, had little\Nexposure to the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.76,0:18:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh often had peculiar requirements.\NWeird food,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,crazy headdresses,\Nodd strange things you had to do and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.08,0:18:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,eat,\Nfunny ways to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.72,0:18:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all form. Huh? What you're\Nseeking is the formless which is a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.28,0:18:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,realization. It's an awareness which\Ncomes upon you. It's like a cloud that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.28,0:19:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,envelops you. See, people think\Nenlightenment is over here and I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.12,0:19:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to grab it. Yeah.\NIt's like a cloud, a myasma that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,gradually takes you over and then\Nsuddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.44,0:19:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,how long does it take to get from down\Nhere
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.88,0:19:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to way up there?\NTenth of a second. Tenth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.96,0:19:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\Npermission on that one. A tenth of a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.00,0:19:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,second is correct. Resist. Tenth of a\Nsecond is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.08,0:19:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One instant.\NIt's this way. The next instant
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.60,0:19:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a totally different universe.\NTakes one/10enth
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.12,0:20:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,1/100th of a second one 10,000th of a\Nsecond. That's all. the longer it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.67,0:20:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So why worry about lifetimes when it\Nonly takes one 10,000 of a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.64,0:20:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when the willingness is total\Nand complete,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.96,0:20:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,then it happens automatically of its\Nown.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.36,0:20:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens. It's like you pull out the\Nlast prop. You pull out the last prop
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.79,0:20:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the door swings open. Huh? So it\Ndoesn't require effort, doesn't require
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.03,0:20:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering, doesn't require agony,\Ndoesn't require penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.00,0:20:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It also needs a teacher to tell you\Nthat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.67,0:20:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can skip all those steps without\Nfeeling guily.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.08,0:21:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right? So the way from the bottom to\Nthe top is can be very rapid. So people
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.76,0:21:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,get um discouraged. They say, "Well,\NI've been meditating for years and then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.67,0:21:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they're this, they're at this and\Nthey're at that place." Huh? Uh not to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.60,0:21:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,worry.\NConsciousness of its own seeks
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.00,0:21:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the realization\Nof its own selfidentity as the source of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.67,0:21:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,one's own existence.\NThe movement overall of human
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is progressive.\NSo you're going with the stream. For one
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.28,0:21:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,thing, you're going with the stream and\Nnot against the stream. Human
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.84,0:21:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is evolving. And as we\Nsaid before, the last time the last
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,harmonic concordance in October 14th in\NSan Francisco, the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.88,0:22:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind went from 205 to 207\Nuh all by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.32,0:22:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to change the world? The\Nfirst thing you can do is do the world a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.12,0:22:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,favor and and don't try to change it.\NThe naive person tries to change the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.32,0:22:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,world.\NWisdom teaches you to change yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.48,0:22:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Change yourself. You don't have to\Nbother changing the world. And the world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.03,0:22:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is serving its karmic purpose. So why\Nwould you want to change it anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.20,0:22:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you relieved all suffering, all war,\Nall poverty, and all this, there
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.76,0:22:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be any people here.\NWhere would you go to evolve in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.12,0:22:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness? I mean, this is the\Nultimate teaching ground, isn't it? You
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.60,0:22:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can go from people who are lower than a\Nkomodo dragon on their calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.32,0:23:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness uh to Christ himself.\NSo what more do you want here? You've
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.28,0:23:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,got uh a springboard. Here you've got\Nthe uh the perfect school,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.20,0:23:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, a staging area. So I look at\Nhuman population on the earth as a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.15,0:23:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,staging area. Is there anything you want\Nto change about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.24,0:23:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NAs long as I got Pepsi,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.40,0:23:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,espresso, coffee, there nothing I want\Nto change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.32,0:23:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because each thing is serving its\Npurpose. Each thing, each of us is born
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.00,0:23:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,with an already calibratable level of\Nconsciousness. If your calibratable
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.79,0:23:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness is 70,\Nyou're not going to come here if this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.76,0:23:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,has become a celestial realm due to all\Nthe dogooders.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.79,0:24:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This will not be inhabitable by us who\Nare trying to get off being miserable,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.40,0:24:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,cowardly,\Nsneaky cheaters.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.55,0:24:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we going to go\Nto learn that honesty is the best
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.88,0:24:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,policy?\NWhere's this guy here gonna go? He needs
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.27,0:24:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Enron and Worldcom,\NMartha Stewart. He needs those people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.91,0:24:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,need that. Where else are you going to\Ncrash?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.72,0:24:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You run this number is about 190. They\Nrun about 190. You run 190 to its
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.96,0:24:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimate end and then you hit the wall.\NBang. You hit the wall. That's the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.32,0:24:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose of it. So if we didn't have an\NEnron or a Worldcom or whatever, we'd
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.60,0:24:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have to create one.\NSo we can stop uh making the world wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.27,0:24:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and being judgmental about it if we see\Nthat it serves the ultimate karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.88,0:25:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose.\NFree will choice is so unlimited because
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.79,0:25:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a whole panorama.\NYou can go down here
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.76,0:25:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from\Nkilling yourself and a busload of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.64,0:25:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,children in the name of God\NIn the name of God, you're going to blow
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.44,0:25:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,up a busload of children. That's a tough\None to sell yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.36,0:25:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I by doing that I go to heaven,\Nthen screw you kids
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.64,0:25:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because I got 30 virgins waiting for me.\NHe's going to blow up a busload of kids
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.32,0:25:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can have 20 virgins\N>> or was 75 virgins. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.44,0:26:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N>> 75 for young guys, 20 version.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.64,0:26:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing they they don't tell you\Nis that those virgins are 900 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.67,0:26:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,too.\Nand they're ugly and toothless.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.27,0:26:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And they hate men.\NI got you, Dary.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.55,0:26:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't tell them those are the\Nvirgins.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.32,0:26:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one reason they're a\Nvirgin.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.64,0:26:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd you get there after blowing out the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.24,0:26:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,bustle of the kids and they say, "Okay,\Nto Okay, boy. Go to it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.52,0:27:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to it.\NAnd you better perform or else.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.36,0:27:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No Playboy magazines in heaven." No.\NSo from the from the most the lowest
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.40,0:27:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what we look at as the lowest levels of\Nconsciousness then which are primarily
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.79,0:27:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,primitive the residual of the animal\Nbrain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.44,0:27:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with an animal brain is\Nwhen you put a prefrontal cortex on it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.32,0:27:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,now it becomes a very clever animal.\NNow you teach this clever animal with a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.55,0:27:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,brain of a\Ndinosaur
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.20,0:27:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,religion.\NThat's what you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.03,0:27:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a dinosaur brain. You've taught\Nit religion and now it eats you in the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.15,0:28:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,name of God.\NThat's the condition of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.20,0:28:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So\Non the one hand it's humorous you know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.20,0:28:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,when you put it all together\Nand because all of it is humorous
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.79,0:28:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if it was reality it would be sad but\Nit's not reality and that's why people
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.48,0:28:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,come here is to discover\Nuh what is re real and what is not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.64,0:28:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Each and everything then fits together\Nuh perfectly. The karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.67,0:28:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,debt of the 30 children in the bus just\Ngot paid off.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.84,0:28:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Bumped, right?\NSo each thing is perfectly in accord
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.00,0:28:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with everything else.\NThat which gets blown up had the karma
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.84,0:29:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting blown up or it couldn't have\Nbeen blown up. Right? Because nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.36,0:29:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,happens by accident.\NThe in infinite field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.55,0:29:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is like an infinite electrostatic\Nmagnetic field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.44,0:29:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one that comes in has a karmic\Ninheritance of karmic pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.36,0:29:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,within that infinite field. Then the\Nkarmic pattern can only go where the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.88,0:29:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,pattern takes it.\NAn iron filing cannot defy a giant
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.91,0:29:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,electromagnetic field of infinite power.\NThe iron filing can't say I've decided I
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.84,0:29:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to go this way.\NI've decided I don't want to go this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.32,0:29:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,way.\NNow
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.36,0:29:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,each thing can only be then the\Nfulfillment of its own karmic propensity
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.48,0:30:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore everything is in accord\Nwith everything else in an absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.20,0:30:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection.\NTo see imperfection then is a projection
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.03,0:30:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the dance of Shiva.\NThen how you see it is it terrible is it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.36,0:30:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful is it terrible is it wonderful\Ndepends if I want it and if I don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.67,0:30:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it terrible if I like it it's wonderful\Nthat out there is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.67,0:30:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,hasn't moved at all.\NIt's the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.64,0:30:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we become then the reflection of that\Nwhich we hold
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.64,0:30:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with reverence.\NTherefore to re revere those qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.72,0:30:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,means you automatically in due time\Nbecome them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.67,0:31:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you hold in mind.\NThat which you worship, that which you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.00,0:31:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,deify,\Nuh that is what you become. That's what
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.24,0:31:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you reflect by choice.\NThere's an infinite field of infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.15,0:31:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,frequencies and vibrations that\Naccompany all these attitudes and views
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.24,0:31:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and emotions.\NSo what happens is that you become the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.60,0:31:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic consequence. You become the\Nreflection of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.44,0:31:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No longer a person.\NStop thinking about yourself as a person
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.55,0:31:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or an identity\Nbecause you aren't that anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.48,0:31:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a karmic windup toy. Let loose.\NKarmic windup toy. let loose in a world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.55,0:32:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite possibilities\Nand infinite gradations of energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.12,0:32:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So you automatically float to the locust\Nof maximum benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.39,0:32:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is born under circumstances\Nthat are karmically perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.36,0:32:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got a resentment about the\Ncircumstances of your birth?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.88,0:32:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you've been to the lecture before,\Neh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.96,0:32:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, the circumstances of your\Nbirth are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.24,0:32:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever impairments you have, whatever\Nthe circumstances, they are the most
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.27,0:32:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,propitious for your own karmic benefit.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.64,0:32:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why self-pity\Nuh is invalid because you don't know it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.67,0:32:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're born with a certain\Ncalibrated level consciousness under
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.27,0:32:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances that are most propitious\Nfor that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.03,0:32:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if that's the fact for you, then\Nit's a fact for everyone. It's a fact
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.79,0:33:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for everyone.\NYou you left people to die of starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.20,0:33:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and slaughtered them mercilessly, then\Nyou're going to get born in a place
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.32,0:33:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,where you left to die of starvation and\Nslaughtered mercilessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.76,0:33:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you just undid that.\NSo then you see that the world is like a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.27,0:33:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,theater of maximum benefit.\NYou see that you have the option to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.24,0:33:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,stop identifying as an isolated person,\Nyou know, a linear
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.12,0:33:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,definition\Nand become just the reflection of the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.60,0:33:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities that you respect.\NIf you respect honesty, hard work and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.00,0:33:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility, then you'll\Nautomatically be to work on time. You'll
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.72,0:33:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically finish the project. You\Nautomatically give the boss his due for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.84,0:34:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your pay etc. You automatically become\Nintegrity. If integrity is what you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.55,0:34:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,value, you become that.\NNow as you become generosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.35,0:34:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness,\Nthe desire to see the sacredness of all
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.83,0:34:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of life, the sacredness of all of life\Nbegins to reveal itself to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.28,0:34:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas\Nis the joy of life coming through that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.72,0:34:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,birdness.\NThe bird has learned that it's part of a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.67,0:34:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship.\NThe new game is I tap on the branch
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.07,0:34:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with a pin and he and she tap tap tap\Nwith her nose. Bump bump bump. First
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.83,0:34:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,time she did that, I'm sitting in the\Nchair. She goes bump bump bump. I said
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.52,0:35:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,h. So I went over and took my pen. I\Nwent bump bump. She went
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.92,0:35:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy of discovery of relationship,\Nmeaningfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.76,0:35:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,significance.\NImmediately she was a somebody to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.72,0:35:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, and of course the joy was\Nequal on this side because now I
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.72,0:35:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,realized I was a somebody to her.\NSo we just birthed a meaning meaningful
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.07,0:35:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship.\Nin which you intuit it the other the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.35,0:35:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,other being's joy.\NSo then life becomes the unfolding of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.35,0:35:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,endless discovery and joy of kindness\Nand love and responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.04,0:35:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and um\Nso you don't have to fight your way up
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.76,0:35:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the ladder of consciousness which keeps\Ndisappearing on me. Every time I turn my
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.04,0:36:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,back on you notice that it disappears.\NIt does that. I've got this wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.40,0:36:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this is now this is a real one\Nthe calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.28,0:36:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nas I remember way back in the 70s it got
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.96,0:36:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered back in the 70s and uh so I\Nstarted to calibrate these are out of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.88,0:36:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,psychoanalysis uh\NColumbia University psychoanalytic uh
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.24,0:36:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,school these are um emergency emotions\Nand these are the welfare emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.32,0:36:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,classified by Shandra back in the 30s\Nalso by young by by everyone uh it's the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.04,0:36:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,perennial philosophy this\Nuh the way these levels lay out are in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.48,0:36:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,accord with the perennial philosophy\Nwhich is very ancient mankind is always
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.92,0:37:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,considered\Num the stratification of these qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.92,0:37:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh pretty much in that way. And you'll\Nnotice that hell is at the bottom of the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.20,0:37:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,chart and divinity is at the top. It's\Nextremely important to notice that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.88,0:37:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to God through shame, guilt,\Nsackcloth, and ashes,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.80,0:37:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,grief, fear of God,\Nanger at God, and pridefulness in how
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.35,0:37:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,religious you are doesn't get you there.\NDoesn't get you there. because
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.40,0:37:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,pridefulness in religion etc is what\Nleads to war.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.00,0:37:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't that religion\Nuh which is very much in the public
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.48,0:37:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,view.\NUh it isn't religion, it's what people
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.20,0:37:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have done with religion, what people\Nhave done with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.52,0:38:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we learn not to blame religion for\Nthe Inquisition and various other
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.44,0:38:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,horrible things in the past as well as\Nthe present. It's what people do with
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.56,0:38:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it. It's what people do with it. You can\Ngive somebody a pillow and they will
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.56,0:38:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy it. Another person will take the\Npillow and smother somebody to death
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.96,0:38:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with it. So it isn't the pillow.\NIt's what you do with it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.32,0:38:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that saves you making various religions\Nwrong. Yeah. Which in today today's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.28,0:38:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,world is a temptation. Every time you\Nsee somebody show blowing off a bomb on
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.64,0:38:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of some religion, you blame it\Non the religion. No, that's the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.32,0:38:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,perversion. That's the misuse. That's\Nthe exploitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.07,0:38:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Um all kinds of things go go on the\Ncamouflage of religion. It's a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.92,0:38:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,camouflage. Camouflage.\NAll right. So at the bottom then we
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.35,0:38:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated all these things. Uh and we\Ndid a scale of one to a thousand. First
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.07,0:39:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I start out mathematically and the\Nnumbers got so huge uh mathematically
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.04,0:39:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I had to switch the\Nlogarithmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.07,0:39:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So the calibrated scale of consciousness\Nuh begins to ascend very rapidly and the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.04,0:39:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,degree of power becomes infinite.\NIt's no longer even trackable.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.76,0:39:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The energies at when they reach a\Ncertain level
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.83,0:39:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,uh become too powerful and too high a\Nfrequency
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.24,0:39:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for the protoplasmic biologic nervous\Nsystem the neuronal structure to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.68,0:39:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore there is the birth of the\Npure not the birth but the emergence of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the atheric body which is\Nnonprotoplasmic
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.92,0:39:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,concordant with the physical brain and\Nwe call it the spirit. This happens at
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.07,0:40:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 200.\NSo at 200 you see a whole change of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.24,0:40:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,quality.\NYou see the courage to face the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.35,0:40:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to face the truth. And\Nyou see that the c
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.20,0:40:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what's going on in consciousness is\Nempowerment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.96,0:40:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So from here down you have force.\NForce people have to resort to force
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.35,0:40:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't have power.\NBecause they don't have power and they
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.88,0:40:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,envy power. So they think they can get\Npower by getting more money or
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.11,0:40:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,uh beating up more people etc.\NIt keeps eluding them because power is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.00,0:40:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of a different quality. Power is of a\Ndifferent quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.28,0:40:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Power then attracts to it exactly that\Nwhich it needs and doesn't have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.88,0:41:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,anything except accept what the world\Noffers. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.48,0:41:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is all seekingness and gain and\Neven if it's successful it lead then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.40,0:41:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to an ego inflation called pride\Nnarcissistic
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.11,0:41:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,over evaluation of oneself and\Narrogance. Arrogance
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.35,0:41:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and the downside of that is of course\Nuh quite painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.80,0:41:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we cross over 200 and that that is the\Ncritical point critical point we know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.16,0:41:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that in America 51% of the people now\N51% of people America calibrate over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.11,0:41:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,51%.\NThe chances of meeting somebody who's
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.35,0:41:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous now are 50/50\Nthat's pretty good
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.07,0:41:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,5050.\NIn the rest of the world, the chances
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.80,0:42:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are only 15%. The chances in the world\Nare 85%
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.92,0:42:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world caliber rates below 200. So\Nthere's no point be bemoning the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.76,0:42:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When you read the paper, just tell\Nyourself that's what the world below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.56,0:42:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like.\NWhat did you think it was going to be? A
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.31,0:42:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,fairy dance?\NThose who live below 200 kill each other
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.59,0:42:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,routinely.\NAnd if you try to stop them from killing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.64,0:42:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,each other, they will hate you.\NThey will hate you. They live off of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.76,0:42:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They live out of hatred. They live out\Nof the spleen. And that's their
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.07,0:42:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,livelihood. That's their\Nself-identification.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.48,0:42:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nyou can't really deprive them of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.11,0:42:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find that out. Try to get\Nsomebody to stop feeling sorry for
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.64,0:43:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,themsel, you know how difficult that is.\N50 years in psychiatry, the toughest job
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.24,0:43:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in all 50 years\Nuh was to get people off the victim
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.04,0:43:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,martyr role. They cling to it. I mean,\Nthey cling ten to nasciously. And if you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.56,0:43:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to threaten it, they become very\Nhostile.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.07,0:43:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the victim of how my mother treated\Nme. I am the victim of how my husband
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.52,0:43:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,did to me. I'm the victim of society.\NUh victimhood, that's the biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.92,0:43:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,addiction in our world. People think\Nit's alcohol and drugs. Forget alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.35,0:43:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and drugs. They're nothing compared to\Nvictimhood. Victimhood. People cling to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.92,0:43:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it. Cling to it. Cling to it. Injustice.\Nvictimhood and injustice without which
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.72,0:43:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't blame anybody. So\Nwith nobody to blame, no injustice and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.07,0:43:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,no vict victimhood and no martyrdom.\NDoc tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.52,0:44:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,now that's the hardest one to get people\Noff of it because it the ego thrives on
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.00,0:44:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it. The ego thrives on injustice\Nand blame and self-pity and martyrdom
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.96,0:44:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and victimhood.\NThe perpetrator victim model which is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.76,0:44:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,very popular in society.\NI mean the doorways to victimhood are
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.07,0:44:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,jammed\Nthe society for this and that you know
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.28,0:44:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of things all victimhood.\NOkay. So then we get beyond that and we
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.40,0:44:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,own that we're just getting we're ju\Nwe're juicing it. The ego loves to juice
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.28,0:44:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,negativities. That's why it's hard to\Nget people off anger, hatred, blame. 30
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.80,0:44:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,years later they're still hating and\Nblaming a person for something. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.56,0:44:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because the ego gets so much juice out\Nof it. That's the only juice the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.11,0:45:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,gets is the juice of negativity. And you\Nwant to take it away from them. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.00,0:45:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,why they get angry at you. So, America\Nis about as popular in waring parts of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.28,0:45:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the world as you would be if you go down\Nthe block, you hear a waring uh couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.16,0:45:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you hear a couple down the\Nblock, I hate you, Harry. I hate you,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.96,0:45:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jenn Genevie. You know, say you run down\Nthe block to help with these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.56,0:45:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing that happened, you're going\Nto have a black guy. They're having you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.96,0:45:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,arrested.\NWhat's he doing here? Oh, he's the one
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.20,0:45:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you're having. I think you're you went\Ndown to help the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.00,0:45:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh I found it's best to go there when\Nthey invite you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.44,0:45:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and take a third party with you better.\NAll right. So integrity then we enter a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.20,0:45:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,whole different uh domain. We feel a\Ndifferent responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.07,0:45:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't leave the world with\Npenicellin when nobody's until you know
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.48,0:45:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,till somebody's seen the value of the\Npenicellin because you feel what a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.48,0:45:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility\Nuh you have something you want to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.80,0:46:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of love, out of love then one\Ndoes many things out of love. So you can
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.88,0:46:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,do things out of love that you cannot do\Nout of anything else. Out of love for
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.44,0:46:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,one's fellow. I mean in World War II,\Nyou know, out of love for your your
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.11,0:46:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,comrades, you'll do things that are\Nabsolutely ridiculous. You turn your
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.11,0:46:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the enemy and take a riddle full\Nof bullets and and you'll take risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.96,0:46:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll do things for love that you\Nwouldn't do for anything else. It's not
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.00,0:46:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,bravery. It's not courage. It's because\Num really love uh interestingly enough
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.16,0:46:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of uh men in the military for\Neach other or women now calibrates at
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.20,0:46:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,510.\N510 there's it's the sound of bag pipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.44,0:46:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of bag pipes. You wonder that\Nyou feel that the hair go up in the back
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.28,0:46:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of head. So we calibrated it in\NScotland. It's 510.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.52,0:47:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,At 510, you lay down your life for your\Nbrother.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.35,0:47:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Profound\Nuh brotherly love. True brotherly love.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.72,0:47:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Loving the other person\Nas yourself really. So it's a very
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.56,0:47:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced.\NSo that's one of the purposes served by
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.68,0:47:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the military is you jump over 200 and\Nwill now do things out of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.59,0:47:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,love, and courage. So you see,\Neverything serves something. Everything
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.52,0:47:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,serves something. So you can't say,\N"Isn't that terrible? They're at war
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.52,0:47:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with each other. Where's this guy going\Nto cross the line?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.20,0:47:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He left the last time out of Cardis.\NThis time he's going to come back. If I
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.59,0:47:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,got to walk into the bullets, the hell\Nwith it." So you walk into the bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.59,0:47:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You literally walk in and you got to\Nliterally walk into the bullets. And as
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.68,0:47:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you leave the body, you made it.\NYou made it. And all your buddies are
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.44,0:48:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there, too.\NInstant recognition. I remember doing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.72,0:48:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that in the Crusades, you know. And I\Ntold you about that guy. Boy. Boy, I
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.04,0:48:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,really put it through him. And he put it\Nthrough me. And we looked at each other
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.52,0:48:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and like\NI did it for Jesus. He did it for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.24,0:48:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, we both broke into circle laughter.\NAll right. So, you you go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.24,0:48:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it. I did it for Jesus, too.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.07,0:48:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And he did it for all, too. I mean, he\Nwas no uh he was very ferocious. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.28,0:48:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he was a son of a gun. All right. So\Nthat's how we transcend the scale of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.52,0:48:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nis the willingness to be the field, the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.76,0:48:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness to let go positionalities.\NUh the the need to be right. It isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.48,0:49:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just being right. It's like you need to\Nbe right. You see how how that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.00,0:49:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,wantingness it's like needing. I need to\Nbe right. I need to be respected. I need
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.11,0:49:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to make money. I need to be a success.\NSo, it's that neediness. It's the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.68,0:49:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,neediness that you get off.\NInstead, you become that which attracts
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.55,0:49:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,those things. You become that which is\Nattracts those things. You build a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.44,0:49:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,better mousetrap and the world will come\Nto your door. I guarantee it. I
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.64,0:49:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,guarantee it. Guarantee it. You become\Ntrustworthy,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.68,0:49:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasant, cheerful.\NUh,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.31,0:49:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and when they call the cleaning service,\Nthey say, "I want so- and so. She's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.76,0:49:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,terrific. She's terrific." We had a\Ncouple recently that I thought were just
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.40,0:49:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,great, you know, and we wanted them. So,\Nyou become that which would attract that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.07,0:49:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which you wish to be and then\Nautomatically discover that you already
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.40,0:50:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,are it.\NYou don't have to seek it. You already
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.72,0:50:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are that. I mean, you'd tap back to\Nbroccoli, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.28,0:50:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli goes\Nand you're sitting there. You go, hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.24,0:50:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you just got it, right? You\Ndon't have to struggle to be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.68,0:50:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Struggle to be that. You already are\Nthat.
